  "texts": [
    "Humans learn and improve through rich feedback from others Take the example of writing an academic paper.",
    "Authors typically write a first draft, seek feedback from their colleagues (informally or through peer review) and improve their paper based on the feedback.",
    "Similarly, when writing new code, developers commonly create a Pull/Merge Request, seek feedback from other developers and improve their code based on the feedback.",
    "Outside of writing a paper/code, even as we are taking significant life decisions (e.g.",
    "choosing a job or PhD program), we first develop an initial inclination, seek feedback from family/friends and update our decision in light of their feedback."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}